lass=title> Re: Best combo</span><hr size=1> Bard songs are fairly easy to resist thou, so dont expect the songs to be too efficient in pvp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 3:54:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ?</span><hr size=1> The bard is not there to deal damage.  He's there to keep you moving (Selos), dispel, and get in the other person's face...leaving you free to nuke.  Then to regen mana/hps when the battle's over.<br>
